  "response": "There are several ways to lock or restrict access to specific webpages on your browser:\n\n1. Browser Extensions:\n- BlockSite (Chrome, Firefox)\n- StayFocusd (Chrome)\n- LeechBlock NG (Firefox)\nThese extensions allow you to set PIN or password protection for specific websites.\n\n2. Parental Control Software:\n- Windows Family Safety\n- Norton Family\n- Kaspersky Safe Kids\nThese provide website blocking and PIN protection\n\n3. Browser Settings:\n- Some browsers have built-in site blocking features\n- You can set up restricted profiles\n\n4. Operating System Restrictions:\n- Windows Parental Controls\n- macOS Screen Time settings\n\n5. Third-Party Apps:\n- Cold Turkey\n- Freedom\n- RescueTime\n\nMost recommended methods:\n- Browser extensions (easy to use)\n- StayFocusd (Chrome)\n- BlockSite (multiple browsers)\n\nRecommended steps:\n1. Choose an extension\n2. Install it\n3. Add websites you want to lock\n4. Set a PIN/password\n5. Configure time restrictions if desired\n\nWould you like me to explain any of these methods in more detail?",
